<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03183</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PRESCRIBING  AN URGENT, COMPREHENSIVE AND INTEGRATED LAND-BASED TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT SYSTEM TO EFFECTIVELY ADDRESS THE TRAFFIC CONGESTION CRISIS IN METRO MANILA, METROPOLITAN CEBU AND METROPOLITAN DAVAO, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to address the crisis brought about by land traffic congestion and gridlock and the shortage of efficient, safe, secure, and accessible mass transportation in metropolitan areas.

Intends to establish a primary policy-making, regulating, enforcement authority under the control and supervision of the Department of Transportation (DOTr) vested with exclusive power to manage and regulate land-based traffic and structures; harmonize all traffic regulations and policies to achieve a comprehensive and integrated statutory and regulatory framework for land-based traffic system; modernize and streamline the mass transportation systems to attain sustainable and safe networks of public transportation; institute a system of accountability for all land-based traffic stakeholders; and
ensure transparency and accountability and compliance with applicable legal requirements in the execution of all projects for the purpose of alleviating the land-based traffic crisis.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : "Traffic Crisis Act"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VELASCO, LORD ALLAN JAY Q.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Nieto (000 2020-03-04)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2019-08-05</td></tr></table>